Biologic interventions for fatigue in rheumatoid ar-
thritis 
 
Authors' conclusions 
 
Treatment with biologic interventions in patients with 
active RA can lead to a small to moderate improvement 
in fatigue. The magnitude of improvement is similar for 
anti-TNF and non-anti-TNF biologics. However, it is un-
clear whether the improvement results from a direct ac-
tion of the biologics on fatigue or indirectly through re-
duction in inflammation, disease activity or some other 
mechanism. 
 
