Thermal ablative therapies for treatment of localised 
renal cell carcinoma: a systematic review of the lit-
erature 
 
CONCLUSION:  
Thermal ablative therapies are valid alternatives to par-
tial nephrectomy for the treatment of small renal masses 
in patients unfit for surgery. Prospective long-term data 
will be needed before the indications for their use ex-
pand further. 
 
